---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Jonathan Wrede"
  description="Privacy policy for jonathanwrede.de."
  locale="en"
  canonicalPath="/en/privacy/"
  alternates={{ de: '/datenschutz/', en: '/en/privacy/' }}
>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6">
    <nav class="bg-card p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 text-xs font-mono">
      <a href="/en/" class="text-slate-400 hover:text-accent">
        <i class="fas fa-arrow-left mr-1.5"></i> jonathanwrede.de
      </a>
    </nav>

    <article class="bg-card p-6 md:p-10 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-accent shadow-lg prose prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

      <h2>Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Jonathan Wrede<br />
        Geiststr. 78<br />
        48151 Muenster<br />
        Germany<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:contact@jonathanwrede.de">contact@jonathanwrede.de</a>
      </p>

      <h2>Hosting and Server Logs</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted as a static site with Hetzner and served through Caddy. When you access
        the site, technically necessary server log data is processed, including IP address, date and time
        of access, requested URL, HTTP status, referrer, and user agent. This processing is based on
        Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR for secure and stable website delivery.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        jonathanwrede.de does not set its own tracking cookies and does not use web analytics such as
        Google Analytics. The main pages load icons and styles locally from this site's own build.
      </p>

      <h2>External Media and Links</h2>
      <p>
        Some blog posts may embed externally hosted media, for example demo GIFs from raw.githubusercontent.com.
        Loading such content can transfer your IP address to the respective provider. External links lead
        to third-party services; their own privacy notices apply.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact me by email, your information is processed to handle the request. The legal basis is
        Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR where the request relates to a contract or pre-contractual steps, otherwise
        Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Within the legal requirements, you have rights to access, rectification, deletion, restriction of
        processing, data portability, and objection. You also have the right to complain to a data protection
        supervisory authority.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
